.TH "round_jiffies_up_relative" 9 "round_jiffies_up_relative" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
round_jiffies_up_relative \- function to round jiffies up to a full second
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" round_jiffies_up_relative
.BI "(unsigned long j "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "j" 12
the time in (relative) jiffies that should be rounded
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is the same as \fBround_jiffies_relative\fP except that it will never
round down.  This is useful for timeouts for which the exact time
of firing does not matter too much, as long as they don't fire too
early.
